subSubSection.paragraph:
Female.
Similar to male, except tergite VIII with posterior margin not serrated, but deeply U-shaped and strongly sinuate (
Fig. 6
); tergite IX without ventral struts; each hemisternite IX fused with each ventral lobe of tergite IX, at least on base (
Fig. 7
); spermatheca with L-curved capsule, globose chamber and irregularly twisted duct (
Fig. 8
).
